resource.http://dev.llgc.org.uk/sas/full_text: This 5 Passenger 1910 Pullman touring car was built at the Pullman Motor Car Company in York, PA. It is one of approximately 1000 cars built in 1910 and sold for about $2000. The folding windshield and top were extra for $150.00. This car is powered by a four cylinder engine and uses a cork-faced cone clutch to drive a three-speed selective sliding transmission for forward and reverse. Completely separate dual ignitions are featured, one by magneto and the other by battery.
